  "text": "According to the Prentice model of pollen dispersal and deposition [CITATION_1] , >80% of pine and birch pollen and >95% of spruce pollen is considered to come from within a 14-km radius for a sedimentary basin <1.0 ha [CITATION_2] . Thus, mean tree volume (m 3 ha À1 ) was calculated at 25-m intervals from each pollen-trap location out to 14 km using all the available vegetation data [CITATION_3] .",
